        "content_en": "An atom consists of a nucleus containing protons (positive) and neutrons (neutral), surrounded by electrons (negative). Atomic number Z = number of protons. Mass number A = protons + neutrons. Isotopes are atoms of the same element with different numbers of neutrons.",
        "content_zh": "原子由原子核（包含带正电的质子和中性的中子）和围绕核运动的电子（带负电）组成。原子序数Z = 质子数。质量数A = 质子数 + 中子数。同位素是同一元素具有不同中子数的原子。"
      },
