        "content_en": "Precipitation reactions: formation of an insoluble solid. Solubility rules: all nitrates (NO₃⁻) and alkali metal salts are soluble. AgCl, PbCl₂, BaSO₄, CaCO₃ are sparingly soluble. Redox reactions: electron transfer between reactants. Oxidizing agent: reduced (gains electrons). Reducing agent: oxidized (loses electrons).",
